</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC216577FFB53660A7E477C3FC70827C" blockId="12.[136,1452,928,1351]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">
Diagnosis:—Stem up to 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A6F977C3FE7085E1" box="[405,471,928,955]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
tall, basal leaves 25–42 
<emphasis id="EEEAB965FFB53660A5B277C2FD5685E0" box="[734,753,929,954]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">×</emphasis>
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A59977C3FCC985E1" box="[757,878,928,955]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="10.0">10–17 mm</quantity>
, inflorescence very lax dichasium, cyme, calyx teeth thin and tall, 2.5–4.0 mm, petals pink to whitish, coronal scales 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A43177A7FC1C8585" box="[861,955,964,991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long, obliquely bidentate acute, anthophore 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A7E4778BFF418259" box="[136,230,1000,1027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
long, slightly rough, glabrous, seed globose to subglobose, surface flat, rounded at back, testa cells margin undulating, without tubercles, hilum prominent, pollen pore number 28–33.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC216577FFB53660A7D17053FF7182A4" blockId="12.[136,1452,928,1351]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">
Description:—Annual, stem erect, glandular pubescent. Basal leaves spathulate to oblanceolate, cauline leaves ellipsoid to lanceolate; inflorescence a lax dichasial cyme; calyx nerves inconspicuous, crisped unicellular and sparsely glandular pubescent, inflated in fruit; alar flowers erect, distinctly pedicellate, petals limb white to pinkish, rectangular, limb apex approximately 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A6C070FFFDA482ED" box="[428,515,1180,1207]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
emarginate, coronal scales 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A45370FFFC3A82ED" box="[831,925,1180,1207]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long; capsule ovoid–spheroid, included in the calyx; anthophore 
<quantity id="1B66C892FFB53660A63170A3FE1A8281" box="[349,445,1216,1243]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
glabrous; seeds globose to subglobose, hilum prominent. Pore number of pollen grains 28–33.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC216577FFB53660A7D1716BFDEC8378" blockId="12.[136,1452,928,1351]" box="[189,587,1288,1314]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">
Distribution:—Southwest 
<collectingCountry id="A48925E7FFB53660A68F716BFDE08378" box="[483,583,1288,1314]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
